How Do You Think Technology Affects Dating?

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion, technology can affect dating in multiple ways. It can either affect dating in a positive way or in a negative way depending on your personality. 
In my case, I've found that technology has affected dating in a positive way.
 I have found that being able to communicate with your significant other over the internet or with apps, makes it easier to handle conflicts and things that may upset your partner because you are not face-to-face with them so that eases a lot of the stress and anxiety of the conflicts. 

ecause of technology, I've also found that it's easier to keep your significant other up to date with what you are doing.
